# Styling Guidelines

## CSS Architecture
1. Use CSS Modules for component-specific styles
2. Follow BEM naming convention for class names
3. Keep styles modular and reusable
4. Use CSS variables for theme values

## Best Practices
1. Mobile-first responsive design
2. Maintain consistent spacing using design tokens
3. Use semantic class names
4. Avoid deep nesting of selectors
5. Keep specificity low

## Example Structure
```css
/* componentName.module.css */
.container {
  /* Base styles */
}

.container__element {
  /* Element styles */
}

.container__element--modifier {
  /* Modifier styles */
}
```

## Theme Guidelines
1. Use design tokens for colors, spacing, and typography
2. Maintain dark/light mode compatibility
3. Follow accessibility guidelines for contrast ratios
4. Keep consistent spacing scales

